div.stage:
Scene II. —A Room in Omnium's House, handsomely furnished;
letters, L. and R., on table. Omnium discovered asleep on a sofa; a book is in
his hand, which after a few seconds he lets fall.

sp.p:
Murder! that is something to fear;—and yet I don't know, Herbert;
your means are good: and very soon, when you are a partner in the house, they
will be better; why should you fear any mother-in-law in the kingdom?
